<div class="g12">
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<p>Merano offers a fascinating blend of Austrian and Italian cultures. Our Three Countries Tour takes in Italy, Austria and Switzerland and includes days out to see the very best these beautiful regions have to offer. What will be the highlight of the holiday? Probably we think the ride on the Bernina Express to St. Moritz.</p>
</div>
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<h2>Itinerary</h2>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>DAY 1 SATURDAY</strong></p>
<p>Fly to Verona from a selection of UK regional airports and transfer to Merano and your hotel. In the evening meet your fellow guests and your Inghams Explorer guide.</p>
<p><strong>DAY 2 SUNDAY </strong></p>
<p>A walking tour of Merano and the famous Trauttmansdorff Castle and Gardens. Colourful plants from all around the word thrive and bloom in more than 80 garden landscapes.</p>
<p><strong>DAY 3 MONDAY</strong></p>
<p>A full day tour of the magnificent Dolomites as beautiful in summer as they are in winter. We’ll stop too at Lake Carezza, known as the “rainbow lake” when the sun reflects off the surrounding mountains.</p>
<p><strong>DAY 4 TUESDAY</strong></p>
<p>Today takes us to the regional capital of Bolzano with wine tasting at nearby Lake Caldaro. In Bolzano, visit the Museum of Archaeology to meet Iceman Ötzi, a well preserved mummy dating back to around 3300BC.</p>
<p><strong>DAY 5 WEDNESDAY</strong></p>
<p>We travel to glamorous St. Moritz in Switzerland travelling part of the way on the famous Bernina Express. Along its route the train negotiates 55 tunnels and 196 bridges with ease.</p>
<p><strong>DAY 6 THURSDAY</strong></p>
<p>Over the mighty Brenner Pass today into Austria and the capital of the Tirol, Innsbruck. Plenty of time to explore the historic old Town and see the Golden Roof. On the way back to Merano, we’ll make a stop at Swarowski Crystal World.</p>
<p><strong>DAY 7 FRIDAY</strong></p>
<p>At leisure in Merano.</p>
<p><strong>DAY 8 SATURDAY</strong></p>
<p>Morning transfer back to Verona for your flight home.</p>
<p><em>Flights from Gatwick to Verona. Supplements may apply for other flights.</em></p>
</div>
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<h2>Included Highlights</h2>
<ul>
<li>All tours and entrance fees included</li>
<li>Services of Explorer Guide.</li>
<li>7 nights at the <a data-udi="umb://document/919b13aa1fae4bc68aa9503210e88b44" href="/{localLink:umb://document/919b13aa1fae4bc68aa9503210e88b44}" title="Adria Hotel">4 star Hotel Adria</a> in <a data-udi="umb://document/c5c478381e04431da3f69d8364215ae7" href="/{localLink:umb://document/c5c478381e04431da3f69d8364215ae7}" title="Merano">Merano</a></li>
<li>7 nights half board.</li>
<li>Guided walk around Merano and the Trauttmansdorff Castle and gardens.</li>
<li>Day tour of the Dolomites - considered to be some of the most beautiful mountains in the world - and Lake Carezza.</li>
<li>Visit to Bolzano and Lake Caldaro with wine tasting.</li>
<li>Excursion to St. Moritz with a trip on the Bernina Express travelling the highest railway in the Alps.</li>
<li>Visit to Innsbruck and the famous Swarowski factory.</li>
</ul>
<p>Please note that we act at all times as selling agent for the suppliers of activities &amp; excursions. See our <a href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/legal/terms-conditions">terms &amp; conditions</a>.</p>
<p> </p>
